flowRoot.flowPara: A valid move is any move that doesn't cause the target object or movable objects to collide. An invalid move is any move that causes the target object or movable objects to collide and/or pushes the objects or hand off the table.
Moving forward in this situation is considered an invalid move.
Moving in any direction in these two situations is considered a valid move.
Moving forward or left in this situation is considered an invalid move.
